text: Kunakbayevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Yermolayevsky Selsoviet, Kuyurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 108 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 20 km from Yermolayevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kuyurgazinsky District
title: Kunakbayevo
